HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 606
By Cepicky
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the Columbia State
Chargers men's basketball team upon an
outstanding 2024-2025 season.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly should salute those student athletes
who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true champions of
whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of young men is the Chargers men's basketball
team of Columbia State Community College, whose members have proven themselves to be
the fiercest of competitors and truly worthy of admiration by posting an excellent 27-5 record this
season and winning three titles, the Tennessee Community College Athletic Association
(TCCAA) regular season championship with 15 wins; the TCCAA Tournament championship;
and the Appalachian District championship; and
WHEREAS, Mahki Wright was honored as the TCCAA Tournament's Most Valuable
Player, and he and teammate Thaddeus Johnson were named to the All-TCCAA First Team;
and
WHEREAS, in Appalachian District competition, the Chargers defeated Jackson State
75-66, bested Roane State 74-71 in overtime, and walloped Pellissippi State 72-50 to bring
home the gold and advance to the National Junior College Athletic Association (NJCAA)
Division I National Championship Tournament in Hutchinson, Kansas; and
WHEREAS, Columbia State's Head Coach, Winston Neal, was honored with the
Appalachian Coach of the Year Award at the NJCAA National Championship; and
WHEREAS, the following young men proudly displayed the pedigree of Chargers:
