Jasiyah Suber, Alex Pollard, Kenneth Ellis, Jarrod Taylor, Arnez Anderson, Mahki Wright, Ron
Brisbon, Thaddeus Johnson, Deing Wang, Julius Sisk, Emanuel Allen, Taveon Comage,
Simeon Williams, Terrell Reeves, and Jamison Glass; and
WHEREAS, Columbia State's superb performance would not have been possible without
the expert guidance of Coach Neal and his assistant coaches, Chris Leggett, Arthur Latham,
Tony Sparkman, and Larry Jones; and
WHEREAS, the Chargers were fortunate to enjoy the unfailing support of Columbia
State's President, Dr. Janet Smith; Athletic Director Katie Willingham; Vice President for Student
Affairs Ruth Ann "Cissy" Holt; Student Manager Antonio Ward; and their families, fans, and
community; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Columbia State men's basketball team epitomize all
that is good in today's student athletes, as they have achieved a premier level of success in
competition while exhibiting the highest degree of character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of
young men not only made possible conference and district championships but also surely bode
well for their future success; and
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to acknowledge
and applaud the Columbia State Chargers for their outstanding season on the hardwood; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the coaches and members of the Columbia State
Chargers men's basketball team upon an outstanding 2024-2025 season, which included two
TCCAA championships, the Appalachian District championship, and a berth in the NJCAA
